> Sausage and mash is an absolute classic. But you know how we treat classics at
> HelloFresh, right? We like to give them a bit of a twist and sprinkle some
> healthy magic dust on top. So, here's our sausage with parmesan swede chips.
> What a treat! And don't forget your red onion relish. It's more bangin' than
> bangers and mash, trust us!

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Peel and chop the @swede{1} in half,
then chop into chip shaped pieces roughly the length of your index finger and
1cm wide. Grate the @parmesan cheese{2}, pull the @rosemary{4%sprigs} leaves
off their stalks and roughly chop them.

Put your swede chips on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over some @olive oil{} and
sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{pinch}, a good grind of @black pepper{} and half
your rosemary. Give the tray a good shake and then put in your oven on the
top shelf for ~{20%minutes}. When 20 mins are up, take your swede tray out of
your oven, turn them over, add the parmesan to the baking tray and give it all
a good shake. Pop back into your oven on the top shelf for another
~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, you can tackle the sausages. Place the @pork & oregano sausages{4}
onto another baking tray, prick them each a couple of times with a sharp
#knife{} or #fork{} and put them in your oven on the second shelf for
~{30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

== Red Onion Relish ==

Now you can prepare the red onion relish and veggies. Chop the @red onion{1}
in half through the root, peel and slice thinly into half moon shapes. Peel
and finely chop the @garlic clove{1}(finely chopped).

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} on low heat in a #non-stick saucepan{}. Add in
your red onion with a sprinkling of @?sugar{} (if you have some) and a pinch of
salt and pepper. Cook slowly for ~{10%minutes}, stirring occasionally and then
add the @balsamic vinegar{1} and continue cooking gently for another
~{10-15%minutes}. When your onion is looking lovely and caramelised, put a
lid on the pan and leave to the side until everything else is ready.

== Tenderstem & Dressing ==

About 7 mins before everything is ready, add a splash of @olive oil{} to a
#frying pan{} on medium heat and add your @tenderstem® broccoli{1} in half
lengthways and the rest of your rosemary. Stir-fry for ~{5%minutes} before
adding your garlic and stir-frying for a further ~{1%minute}.

Serve your sausages with your swede chips, stir-fried tenderstem broccoli and
red onion relish on the side. Enjoy!